title: For Sale:  S&W .45 Shield
postcontent: I got this a few weeks ago, as I really like the one I have in .40.I didn't really need another, just like having a .45. But it shoots almost exactly like my .40, same trigger, same accuracy, almost the same recoil.The .45 Shields are slightly larger and fatter than the 9mm and .40 Shield, just enough so that many holster models don't fit either size.So my holsters for the .40 don't fit the .45, I'd have to buy new ones.Plus I now have to keep .45 ammo on hand, where before all I had was .40.The .45 does have better stippling for a better grip than the .40, also the .45 has a better thumb safety. It sticks out a bit more, has more travel, and clicks on and off positively, where my .40 safety is mushy.I've fired a 100 round box of Winchester FMJ, and about 15 rounds of Federal JHP through it, not even broken in yet.It comes with the box, lock, papers and the two magazines, one 6 round and one 7 round. Add one in the chamber, and you have a nice thin 7 or 8 shot .45.These have great triggers for a polymer gun, and the Shield is nice and compact for concealed carry.I would consider trading someone for a 9mm Shield, either the standard one or the Performance Center 9mm Shield, as I want to get one of those for my daughter.  She's small, and I think she would do better with a 9mm than the .40 or .45.

Do you have pictures of 28 inch barrel  maverick?Scammers: I just didScammers: check your emailMe: Got itScammer: You like it?Me: Why do the pictures you sent me come from old listings on on gunauction[dot com]?Scammer: Hmmm.
